Seasoned actress and musician Marah Louw has dumped acting for politics after she joined Hlaudi Motsoeneng's African Content Movement (ACM). Louw is sitting second behind party president Motsoeneng on the party's national list, meaning that if the green horns were to secure two seats or more, the former Idols judge will be a lawmaker after the May 8 polls. TO READ MORE ON THIS STORY GET A COPY OF TODAY'S SUNDAY WORLD.